Ask HN: Why is Prime Video so bad at keeping audio/video in sync?
text:
It’s kind of surreal how bad Amazon is at streaming their own content over their own network onto their own hardware.

I’ve tried watching the newest season of Jack Ryan and the A/V sync is completely out of whack. I even tried watching a pirated copy and that too was out of sync in the same exact way. It’s genuinely funny and frustrating.

Generative “Choose your own adventure” with ChatGPT prompt
text:
Super fun prompt that you can customize to your persuasion:

“ You are the narrator of a story, beginning with the reader waking up on a spaceship that has crashed on an unknown planet. I am the reader. For each response until I say otherwise, Tell me what happens based on my last answer, and ask me what to do next from two or three choices. For the first response tell me more about the scene.‘

Enjoy
